An organisation has condemned mismanagement of children&rsquo;s homes. The Love for Child Association chairman Nelson Mwangi said most children in the homes lead miserable lives.&ldquo;Some homes are well-funded by donors and sponsors but their managers misuse the funds and other resources donated to them by well-wishers,&rdquo; he said. Mwangi spoke at the Liberty Children&rsquo;s Home in Mlolongo town on Saturday.His organisation donated beds, metal boxes, bed sheets, mattresses and food.The home has more than 50 orphans and vulnerable children.